<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880714-0146 </DOCNO><HL> Sandamp;P Revises 500-Stock Index </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CLO MO MIL WTHG </CO><IN> NDX BCY </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard andamp; Poor's Corp. said it dropped Coleco Industries Inc. and Mohasco Corp. from its index of 500 stocks.    Sandamp;P said it is replacing the two companies with Millipore Corp., a Bedford, Mass., industrial company, and Worthington Industries Inc., a Columbus, Ohio, steel concern.    Coleco is in bankruptcy-law proceedings under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code, and Mohasco is being acquired. </TEXT></DOC>